  "description": "Perennial shrubby pepper (Capsicum chinense, 90–150+ days to first fruit) producing small lantern-shaped intensely pungent fruit (100,000–350,000 SHU). Requires warm climate (zones 9–11 for reliable fruiting); slow to establish; benefits from starting very early (12 weeks before last frost). Self-incompatible flowering in some cultivars; grow multiple plants for best yields. Prune to shrub form for multi-season production in warm climates.",
